Priscilla Nash Brennan Edit Profile

literature educator researcher English educator

Priscilla Nash Brennan, American psychology eduator, English educator, researcher, literature educator, educator. volunteer mental health aide, library aide, Big Sister; teacher Catholic Christian doctrine; board directors Catholic Charities North Suburban Boston. Member American Association of University Women, American Psychological Association, Marblehead Chamber of Commerce, Boston Yacht Club (Marblehead).

Background

Brennan, Priscilla Nash was born on August 21, 1948 in Leominster, Massachusetts, United States. Daughter of Wallace Edward and Jean Catherine (Maxellon) Nash.

Education

Bachelor of Science in Psychology, Fitchburg (Massachusetts) State College, 1978. Master of Education in Community Counseling, Salem (Massachusetts) State College, 1991.

Career

Owner, operator, From Grandmother with Love, Harbor Proofs teacher, various community colleges instructor, Marian Court College, Swampscott, Massachusetts, since 1992; instructor, North Shore Community College, Lynn, Massachusetts, since 1996.

Achievements

Membership

Volunteer mental health aide, library aide, Big Sister. Teacher Catholic Christian doctrine. Board directors Catholic Charities North Suburban Boston.

Member American Association of University Women, American Psychological Association, Marblehead Chamber of Commerce, Boston Yacht Club (Marblehead).

Interests

Avocations: boating, sewing, gardening, baking, theater.
